The very ancient Greek colony of Massilia, rival of Carthage sor the commerce of the Mediterranean‚ entered at a very early date into friendly relations with Rome, which were never disturbed till 49 B.c. when the city was besieged by Caesar 3 (cf. The bond of union between the two cities was common hostility to the Gauls and Carthaginians.
